<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871223-0174 </DOCNO><HL> Letters to the Editor:Politicians' BlindnessToward Business</HL><DD> 12/23/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><TEXT>   Small wonder the private and public sectors are light years apart on such important issues as balanced budgets, trade deficits and future economic direction necessary to ensure a vital America in the 21st century. When asked what they'd do if not in politics, not one of the 12 candidates previewed in The Wall Street Journal's special report &quot;Politics 88&quot; (Dec. 4) would be a businessman. I'm certainly not opposed to teaching, foreign service, religion or show business, but who and what is going to pay for these not-for-profit services?    Patrick J. McKeever   Indianapolis</TEXT></DOC>